Xylem Inc. (XYL) Shares Sold by Daiwa SB Investments Ltd.

					Posted by Francis Steltz on Jul 21st, 2017 // No Comments 



Daiwa SB Investments Ltd. reduced its stake in shares of  Xylem Inc. (NYSE:XYL) by 10.2% during the second quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the SEC. The fund owned 24,354 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after selling 2,781 shares during the period. Daiwa SB Investments Ltd.’s holdings in Xylem were worth $1,350,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
A number of other large investors also recently bought and sold shares of the stock. Federated Investors Inc. PA boosted its stake in  Xylem by 30.7% in the fourth quarter. Federated Investors Inc. PA now owns 12,105 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $600,000 after buying an additional 2,842 shares during the last quarter.  GSA Capital Partners LLP bought a new stake in  Xylem during the fourth quarter valued at $224,000.  Numeric Investors LLC bought a new stake in  Xylem during the fourth quarter valued at $525,000.  Quadrature Capital Ltd bought a new stake in  Xylem during the fourth quarter valued at $4,626,000.  Finally, Perigon Wealth Management LLC bought a new stake in  Xylem during the fourth quarter valued at $586,000. Hedge funds and other institutional investors own  85.51% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Xylem Inc. alerts:



Xylem Inc. (XYL) traded up 1.07% during mid-day trading on Friday, hitting $57.54. 287,836 shares of the stock were exchanged. The company has a market capitalization of $10.34 billion, a PE ratio of 41.40 and a beta of 1.18. The stock has a 50 day moving average price of $54.55 and a 200 day moving average price of $50.91. Xylem Inc. has a 1-year low of $45.60 and a 1-year high of $57.55. 




Xylem (NYSE:XYL) last issued its quarterly earnings results on Tuesday, May 2nd. The industrial products company reported $0.39 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, beating the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $0.38 by $0.01. The firm had revenue of $1.07 billion during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $1.05 billion. Xylem had a return on equity of 15.53% and a net margin of 6.75%. The company’s revenue for the quarter was up 26.4% on a year-over-year basis. During the same quarter last year, the company posted $0.35 EPS.  On average, equities analysts anticipate that  Xylem Inc. will post $2.31 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
The company also recently announced a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Wednesday, June 21st. Investors of record on Thursday, May 25th were given a $0.18 dividend. The ex-dividend date of this dividend  was Tuesday, May 23rd. This represents a $0.72 dividend on an annualized basis and a yield of 1.26%. Xylem’s payout ratio is 50.35%. 
